author: blair
msg: On the file externals branch.
File externals now place into the working copy a file.  Lots of work
to do, but the file now appears just as a switched file.  Removing the
external from the svn:externals now removes it from the working copy
if there are no modifications to it, otherwise it leaves it with mods.
* subversion/libsvn_client/externals.c
(switch_file_external):
New function that is very similar to switch_dir_external(), except it
creates an empty file and adds it into a working copy.  If the
file already exists, just switch to the proper URL.
(handle_external_item_change):
For each of the major code paths, checking out/exporting, updating
and removing, handle a file external.
